      "side": 1,
      "message": "Should we make this behaviour conditional?\n\nCurrently you suggest to ignore data beyond the root SFLV\u0027s value length. While this would give positive decode results in most cases, I think sometimes users would want to pass the exact buffer with BEJ data and see if it is malformed, i.e:\n- print warning if BEJ has data beyond the root SFLV\u0027s value length,\n- return fail if BEJ has data beyond the root SFLV\u0027s value length.",
      "revId": "847b0d518cc7e42dea6674e155baff06b8d560de",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
