      "writtenOn": "2026-05-22T03:03:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The \"trailing data beyond root SFLV value length\" issue is exactly the kind of device quirk we ran into on our PLDM RDE side too.\n\nI implement 3 policies for libbej user\n\n1. existing IgnoresTrailingBytes keeps validating the default lenient behavior.\n2. new WarnsOnTrailingBytes enables warn, asserts decode returns 0, output matches the unpadded reference, and stderr contains the warning (gtest\u0027s CaptureStderr).\n3. new ErrorsOnTrailingBytes enables error, asserts decode returns bejErrorInvalidSize.",
